a Symfony2 collection.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T23:12:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"petk/awesome-jquery","categoryHTML":"<h2>Server-side Integrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Python:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/django-static-jquery/\">django-static-jquery</a> - jQuery packaged in an handy Django app to speed up new applications and deployment.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T23:12:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"petk/awesome-jquery","categoryHTML":"<h2>Server-side Integrations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Ruby:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rails/jquery-rails\">jquery-rails</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rails/jquery-rails\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">935</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":935,\"repo\":\"rails/jquery-rails\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A gem to automate using jQuery with Rails.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jquery-ui-rails/jquery-ui-rails\">jquery-ui-rails</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jquery-ui-rails/jquery-ui-rails\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1130,\"repo\":\"jquery-ui-rails/jquery-ui-rails\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - jQuery UI for the Rails asset pipeline.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T23:12:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+FEFF\">U+FEFF</a> ZERO WIDTH NO-BREAK SPACE - it’s name\nsuggests, that it can be used like U+2060 WORD JOINER. And in fact the\nlatter was introduced to inherit its semantics. This is because U+FEFF had\nbecome a special beacon called the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byte_order_mark\">byte order\nmark</a>, that was placed on\nthe beginning of some UTF-8 files. In complying software (including many\ntext editors) this character is stripped from the start of a file and\nhandled as metadata. In non-complying software (like the PHP interpreter)\nthis leads to all sorts of fun behaviour.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T22:58:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Code Points that Affect Others</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1F1E6..U+1F1FF\">Regional Indicator Symbols</a>\nU+1F1E6 to U+1F1FF resemble the 26 latin characters. They are used to\ncreate flag emoji. Since the Unicode consortium didn’t feel like getting on\nboard with international politics, the solution to flags is to combine\nthese 26 characters to the respective ISO code for a country. Examples:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Country</th>\n<th>ISO Code</th>\n<th>Code Points</th>\n<th>Emoji (if supported)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>USA</td>\n<td>US</td>\n<td>U+1F1FA + U+1F1F8</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Germany</td>\n<td>DE</td>\n<td>U+1F1E9 + U+1F1EA</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>China</td>\n<td>CN</td>\n<td>U+1F1E8 + U+1F1F3</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T22:42:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hothero/awesome-rails-gem","categoryHTML":"<h2>Testing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vcr/vcr\">VCR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vcr/vcr\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5444,\"repo\":\"vcr/vcr\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Record your test suite's HTTP interactions and replay them during future test runs for fast, deterministic, accurate tests.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-16T21:21:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hothero/awesome-rails-gem","categoryHTML":"<h2>Coding Style</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/metricfu/metric_fu\">Metric Fu</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/metricfu/metric_fu\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">607</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":607,\"repo\":\"metricfu/metric_fu\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A fist full of 